# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Vercel Speed Insights is **already installed and properly configured** in this project. No changes were necessary.

## Verification Process

### 1. Documentation Review
Fetched the latest official documentation from: https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart

The documentation specifies for Next.js App Router:
- Install `@vercel/speed-insights` package
- Import: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'`
- Add `<SpeedInsights />` component in the root layout (app/layout.tsx) within the body tag

### 2. Current Configuration

**Package Installation:**
- ✅ `@vercel/speed-insights` v2.0.0 is installed (latest version)
- Listed in `package.json` dependencies

**Component Integration:**
- ✅ Correctly imported in `src/app/layout.tsx`: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'`
- ✅ Component properly placed in the root layout within the `<body>` tag
- ✅ Positioned after the children content as recommended

**Code Location:** `typescript-learning-app/src/app/layout.tsx`
```tsx
export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="ja">
      <body>
        <ProgressMerger />
        {children}
        <Analytics />
        <SpeedInsights />  {/* ✅ Correctly configured */}
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

### 3. Verification Tests

All verification steps completed successfully:
- ✅ Type checking: `npm run typecheck` - No errors
- ✅ Linting: `npm run lint` - No errors
- ✅ Build: `npm run build` - Successful compilation
- ✅ Tests: `npm run test` - All 33 tests passed (2 test files)

### 4. Project Details

**Framework:** Next.js 16.2.6 (App Router with Turbopack)
**Package Manager:** npm (package-lock.json present)
**Configuration:** Matches official Vercel documentation requirements

## Conclusion

No code changes were required. The project already has Vercel Speed Insights properly installed and configured according to the latest official documentation. The implementation follows best practices:

1. Latest package version (2.0.0)
2. Correct import path for Next.js
3. Proper component placement in root layout
4. All builds, tests, and linting pass successfully

The Speed Insights functionality is ready to collect performance metrics once deployed to Vercel and enabled in the Vercel dashboard.

## Next Steps (Manual)

To activate Speed Insights on Vercel:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Speed Insights section in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click the "Enable" button
4. Speed Insights will start collecting data after the next deployment
